{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-12-14","name":"Sir Piers de Ros","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Sir Piers de Ros","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Prefix","value":"Sir"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Piers"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Ros"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Peter","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1087–1153","fullLifespan":"1087–1153","memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-68232-494-83/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/30940595","headline":"Piers de LaRoche","description":"The Roche surname is French (Norman) in origin and means \"rock\".  It is both a geographical and habitation surname; it could be acquired by a family who lived near a rocky outcrop or crag, or by livin …","@type":"MediaObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7768-125561-557-94/dist.png?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/175046567","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7768-125561-557-94/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7768-125561-557-94/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"Hamlake Castle, aka Helmsley Castle, Yorkshire, England - Wikipedia","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7768-125561-1575-60/dist.png?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/175046842","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7768-125561-1575-60/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7768-125561-1575-60/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"Helmsley Castle, remodeled by Robert and Everard de Roos, children of Piers and Adeline - Wikipedia","@type":"ImageObject"}],"popularStory":{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-904-68232-494-83/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/30940595","headline":"Piers de LaRoche","description":"The Roche surname is French (Norman) in origin and means \"rock\".  It is both a geographical and habitation surname; it could be acquired by a family who lived near a rocky outcrop or crag, or by livin …","@type":"MediaObject"},"birthDate":"+1087","birthPlace":{"address":"Holderness, Yorkshire, England","geo":{"latitude":53.80918,"longitude":-0.18092,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1153","deathPlace":{"address":"Ros Holderness England","geo":{"latitude":53.83,"longitude":-0.42,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"burialPlace":{"address":"Helmsley, Yorkshire, England","geo":{"latitude":54.24674,"longitude":-1.05576,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Piers de Ros, of Ros, Holderness, Yorkshire, born about 1080, died about 1130:\n\tPiers de Ros (or Roos), born about 1080, would have adopted his surname from Ros, in Holderness in the North Riding of Yorkshire [see Notes on Surname, under the Collaborate tab].  Piers and his son and grandson had been attached to the Count of Aumale, [Normandy, France] who was blood kinsman of William “the Conqueror” and one of the largest magnates of Yorkshire in that period.  Piers was dead about 1130.  Piers’s son Everard (who succeeded Piers as son and heir) styled himself \"Everard son of Peter steward of Holderness\" when he followed the Count of Aumale in making a donation to Bridlington Priory 1135-1139.  \n\nIt is not known if Piers was born in England or might have come across from Normandy.  He must have been intelligent and robust, as he vaulted up in social status through his marriage.  Hamlake Castle, and the Barony of Helmsley, Yorkshire, came into the Ros family through Piers’s wife, married about 1106 [given the probable birth year of their eldest son], England, probably in Yorkshire, England, to Adeline Espec, born about 1088, Yorkshire, England (daughter of Wiliam Espec and his wife Adeline), died before 1155 [she predeceased her brother], England.  The children of Adeline were coheirs with the heirs of her sisters Hawise and Aubrey after the death of their brother Walter Espec in 1155.  It was this Espec family who founded the castles at Helmsley and Wark that passed into the Ros family.  Walter Espec also founded Kirkham Priory (around 1130), and then Rievaulx Abbey (building commencing in 1132, which was a major impetus for the Cistercians coming into England).  \n\nPiers had been a steward (dapifer) of the Count of Aumale, [Normandy, France] (who in English records was known as the Earl of Albemarle).  [A dapifer – the servant that brings the meat to the table at a meal; the official title of the steward in a medieval English nobleman's household].   Stephen (Étienne), Count of Aumale, [Normandy, France] was Lord of Holderness (the region in Yorkshire where Ros was a place).  Stephen was born by 1070, son of Adelaide (sister of William “the Conqueror,” King of England), by her third husband, Eudes, Count of Champagne, who had been granted Holderness by the Conqueror after Domesday Book was drawn up in 1086.  Stephen died between 1119 and 1130, succeeded by his son William “le Gros,” Count of Aumale and Lord of Holderness, who died in 1179.  It is very possible that Piers or his father came to Yorkshire as their steward, as the position passed down in his family.  \n\nReference: Research by Paul C. Reed, FASG for the Burton Family Organization; Roos Family, 9 July 2022, pages 255-256.","sourceList":[{"title":"Piers De Ros, \"Find A Grave Index\"","sourceType":"FSREADONLY","sourceLink":"https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QVG9-Q4J9","sourceUri":"QZZ2-BXD"},{"title":"Our Royal, Titled, Noble, and Commoner Ancestors","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://our-royal-titled-noble-and-commoner-ancestors.com/p810.htm#i24331","sourceUri":"QQ8K-B62"},{"title":"The Peerage","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://www.thepeerage.com/p36886.htm#i368856","sourceUri":"QQ8K-Y63"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"2","year":"1087","date":"1087","place":"Holderness, Yorkshire, England"},{"name":"Alt. Birth","sources":"0","year":"1088","date":"1088","place":"Yorkshire, England","type":"USER_DEFINED","age":"1"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1109","date":"about 1109","place":"Yorkshire, England","age":"22","id":"GZ5D-JYD"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1124","date":"Abt 1124","place":"Helmsley, Yorkshire, England","age":"37","id":"LBXS-JJW"},{"name":"Alt. Death","sources":"0","year":"1130","date":"Bef 1130","place":"Ros, Holderness, Yorkshire, England","type":"USER_DEFINED","age":"42"},{"name":"Death","sources":"1","year":"1153","date":"1153","place":"Ros Holderness England","age":"66"},{"name":"Burial","sources":"1","place":"Helmsley, Yorkshire, England"}],"spouse":[{"name":"Adeline Espec","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1094–1153","birthDate":"A+1094","deathDate":"+1153/","age":60,"@type":"Person","identifier":"LBH8-PQ8","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/LBH8-PQ8/adeline-espec-1094-1153","published":true}],"children":[{"name":"Everard de Ros","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1109–1154","birthDate":"A+1109","deathDate":"A+1154","age":45,"otherParentId":"LBH8-PQ8","@type":"Person","identifier":"GZ5D-JYD","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GZ5D-JYD/everard-de-ros-1109-1154","published":true},{"name":"Robert de Ros","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1124–1162","birthDate":"A+1124","deathDate":"A+1162","age":38,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/4rt7m/thumb64.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"otherParentId":"LBH8-PQ8","@type":"Person","identifier":"LBXS-JJW","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/LBXS-JJW/robert-de-ros-1124-1162","published":true}],"ageAtDeath":66,"@type":"Person","@context":"http://schema.org","identifier":"G9TD-5V7","memories":3,"photos":2,"stories":1,"sources":10,"nameSources":2,"genderSources":1,"url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/G9TD-5V7/sir-piers-de-ros-1087-1153"},"localizedData":{"sq":{"1087–1153":"viti1087–viti1153","1094–1153":"vitit1094–viti1153","1109–1154":"vitit1109–vitit1154","1124–1162":"vitit1124–vitit1162","1088":"viti 1088","1154":"vitit 1154","1087":"viti 1087","1153":"viti 1153","1096":"vitit 1096","1162":"vitit 1162","1094":"vitit 1094","Bef 1130":"para vitit 1130","1106":"vitit 1106","about 1109":"rreth vitit 1109","Abt 1124":"rreth vitit 1124","1124":"vitit 1124","1109":"vitit 1109","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Ros, Holderness, Yorkshire, England":"Holderness, Yorkshire, Anglia, Mbretëria e Bashkuar","Helmsley, Yorkshire, England":"Helmsley, Yorkshire, England","Ros Holderness England":"Holderness, Yorkshire, Anglia, Mbretëria e Bashkuar","Holderness, Yorkshire, England":"Holderness, Yorkshire, England"},"hy":{"1087–1153":"1087–1153","1094–1153":"1094–1153","1109–1154":"1109–1154","1124–1162":"1124–1162","1088":"1088","1154":"1154","1087":"1087","1153":"1153","1096":"1096","1162":"1162","1094":"1094","Bef 1130":"before 1130","1106":"1106","about 1109":"about 1109","Abt 1124":"about 1124","1124":"1124","1109":"1109","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Անգլիա","Ros, Holderness, Yorkshire, England":"Holderness, Yorkshire, Անգլիա, United Kingdom","Helmsley, Yorkshire, England":"Helmsley, Yorkshire, Անգլիա","Ros Holderness England":"Holderness, Yorkshire, Անգլիա, United Kingdom","Holderness, Yorkshire, England":"Holderness, Yorkshire, Անգլիա"},"bg":{"1087–1153":"1087г.–1153г.","1094–1153":"1094г.–1153г.","1109–1154":"1109г.–1154г.","1124–1